<section class="py-24 px-6 opacity-0" data-animate="troubleshooting">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4 text-gray-100">Troubleshooting</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400">Common issues and solutions</p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
      <div class="bg-surface-100 border border-surface-300 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-200 mb-3">🔒 App won't open / blocked by macOS</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-4">
          Ku-Ka is unsigned, so macOS blocks it by default.
        </p>
        <div class="bg-surface-50 border border-surface-200 rounded-lg p-3 font-mono text-sm mb-3">
          <code class="text-accent-light">sudo xattr -d com.apple.quarantine /Applications/Ku-Ka.app</code>
        </div>
        <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm">
          Or go to <strong>System Settings → Privacy & Security</strong> and click <strong>"Open Anyway"</strong>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-surface-100 border border-surface-300 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-200 mb-3">🚫 Shortcut doesn't work</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-4">
          Ku-Ka needs Accessibility permission to intercept <code class="bg-surface-200 px-1 rounded">Shift+Command+4</code>.
        </p>
        <ol class="text-gray-500 text-sm space-y-2">
          <li>1. Go to <strong>System Settings → Privacy & Security → Accessibility</strong></li>
          <li>2. Enable Ku-Ka in the list</li>
          <li>3. Restart Ku-Ka from the menu bar</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-surface-100 border border-surface-300 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-200 mb-3">📸 Black screenshot or capture fails</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-4">
          Screen Recording permission is required.
        </p>
        <ol class="text-gray-500 text-sm space-y-2">
          <li>1. Go to <strong>System Settings → Privacy & Security → Screen Recording</strong></li>
          <li>2. Enable Ku-Ka</li>
          <li>3. Try capturing again</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-surface-100 border border-surface-300 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-200 mb-3">🖼️ Screenshots not saving</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-4">
          Check if the Screenshots folder exists and is writable.
        </p>
        <div class="bg-surface-50 border border-surface-200 rounded-lg p-3 font-mono text-sm mb-3">
          <code class="text-accent-light">mkdir -p ~/Screenshots</code>
          <code class="text-accent-light">chmod 755 ~/Screenshots</code>
        </div>
        <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm">
          Files are saved as <code class="bg-surface-200 px-1 rounded">Screenshot_YYYY-MM-DD_at_HH-MM-SS.png</code>
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-surface-100 border border-surface-300 rounded-xl p-6 md:col-span-2">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-200 mb-3">🔧 Both Accessibility AND Screen Recording Required</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-4">
          Ku-Ka needs <strong>two separate permissions</strong> to work properly. Missing either will cause partial functionality.
        </p>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-4">
          <div class="bg-surface-50 border border-surface-200 rounded-lg p-3">
            <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-200 mb-2">✅ Accessibility Permission</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mb-2">Required for keyboard shortcut interception</p>
            <ol class="text-gray-500 text-sm space-y-1">
              <li>1. <strong>System Settings → Privacy & Security</strong></li>
              <li>2. Click <strong>Accessibility</strong></li>
              <li>3. Enable <strong>Ku-Ka</strong> in the app list</li>
              <li>4. Restart Ku-Ka from menu bar</li>
            </ol>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-surface-50 border border-surface-200 rounded-lg p-3">
            <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-200 mb-2">📸 Screen Recording Permission</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mb-2">Required for actual screen capture</p>
            <ol class="text-gray-500 text-sm space-y-1">
              <li>1. <strong>System Settings → Privacy & Security</strong></li>
              <li>2. Click <strong>Screen Recording</strong></li>
              <li>3. Enable <strong>Ku-Ka</strong> in the app list</li>
              <li>4. Try capturing again</li>
            </ol>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-surface-50 border border-surface-200 rounded-lg p-3">
          <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-200 mb-2">🔍 Quick Permission Check</h4>
          <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mb-2">Run these commands in Terminal to check current status:</p>
          <div class="font-mono text-sm space-y-1">
            <code class="block text-accent-light">tccutil reset Accessibility com.christianvilen.Ku-Ka</code>
            <code class="block text-accent-light">tccutil reset ScreenCapture com.christianvilen.Ku-Ka</code>
          </div>
          <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mt-2">
            Then re-enable both permissions in System Settings. Replace <code class="bg-surface-200 px-1 rounded">com.christianvilen.Ku-Ka</code> with your actual bundle ID if different.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>